`std.format.formattedRead` now only accepts pointers as input arguments.

For example, the "bad" version of the following code lead to very confusing
errors from Phobos.

-------
import std.format;
void main() {
    int[3] row;
    auto text = "10 20 30";
    //formattedRead(text, "%(%d %)", row);   // bad
    formattedRead(text, "%(%d %)", &row);  // OK
}
-------
